I usually do this in the theaters, so that I don't get spoiled by the footage, especially for the blockbuster movies, or movies I want to see. For me, it helps.
author: So Jin Choi

text: Interesting... I usually take a very strong interest in horror movies that show as little as possible in their trailers. The majority of the time, horror movies show pretty much EVERY scare, including their biggest one, in the trailer, for example, Annabelle. Terrible movie, by my standards. The Conjuring on the other hand, had a simple hide and seek game as a trailer with hands clapping, leaving everything else to my imagination. Once I saw the movie, hell, I was on the edge of my seat, jumping, even holding my breath and hearing my heart pounding (think of the scene when the girls are sleeping at night and she sees something in the corner and just loses it). Though this trailer was predictable in both of it's scares with the rope and the stranger creeping, I have hopes that this can be a good horror flick.
